				Karoo National Park outside Beaufort-West

Picture: Riaan Nel
				
		

Extreme weather conditions around South Africa have resulted in heavy rain in some areas – and even snow in others.
At the Karoo National Park outside Beaufort-West, large parts of the park were under water with the Leeu River overflowing on Wednesday.
The heavy rain was followed by snow – first on the mountains surrounding the park, then in the park itself.

